features: Easy Assembly: The Scandinavian style of this shelf makes it suitable to complement all your other furniture. It is very easy to assemble and should take only 10 minutes.
Sturdy and Easy to Clean: You can adjust the legs of the shelf to make it sturdy, and it's very easy to clean with just a rag.
Durable and Eco-Friendly: Our standing book shelves are made of premier metal and high-quality MDF that meet the US CARB P2 standard, so you don't have to worry about bad smells.
Dimensions: 35.43"W x 11.81"D x 51"H. The height between bookshelves is 12.2 inches, so you can organize your photo albums, home and office decor, wine, books, food, and more.
Warranty: We provide a minimum of 1 year warranty for all our metal decorative book shelf. If you have any questions or concerns, we will be there to assist you.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Nice Looking and Sturdy
reviews.reviewText: I ordered four of these during Prime Days because they looked nice and the size was right for the knee wall in our upstairs hallway. They were easy to put together without the instructions, since they were in another language. It took about fifteen to twenty minutes each shelf. They look nice together and are able to hold the books that I own no problem. The color of the shelves is consistent on each set that we purchased.Fir those who are complaining that it isn't wood, if you read the description you would have known that it was MDF not actual wood shelves. The price was worth it, the shelves are very sturdy and do not sway or rock with the weight I have on them with the books. I would purchase them again if I run out of space.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Very nice shelf. Looks good, even better in person than on the website. The boards are thick and look good. The black metal frame is very sturdy and strong. Assembly was fairly easy. All the board holes lined up with the frame holes. The instructions were not very good, but with a little common sense it worked out okay. Overall it's a good purchase. Worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I like this shelf very much because it is used by me to put my plants on the balcony. I like shopping online very much, which makes me feel very convenient. For me, this installation is relatively simple. I bought two identical shelves for my plants. The height is also very suitable. Both sides and the back are reinforced, Of course, this is also the most attractive thing for me. I am very afraid that my potted plant will fall when placed on it. I like to raise some potted plants and take good care of them. They can provide me with good companionship. Each layer can accommodate three pots of green plants, although there is a need for spacing between them. However, just placing my potted plants looks a bit monotonous. I also decorated the four legs of the rack, which looks great. This is an open shelf, and I placed it against the wall so that my potted plants can be exposed to the sun without worrying about falling off.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Attractive, solid, good value
reviews.reviewText: We are very pleased with our purchase. The shelves are engineered wood but are not only solid but attractive. We bought this primarily as a storage shelf but wanted it to look attractive in home office space. The assembly was easy with only the tools provided. Pay attention to the holes on the metal frame so that you don't reverse any piece as the back cross brace needs to be attached.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Worth every penny....but.
reviews.reviewText: I really like this 5 tier shelf. Its very sturdy and nice looking. Went together very easy EXCEPT one of the 4 adjustable feet were bent from the factory and would not thread into female part of the cabinet. I tried to move to another leg but it was the same. I had to go to my local Lowes and found something very similar and it worked just fine. Besides that minor problem it would of received 5 stars from me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works very well
reviews.reviewText: Looks perfect in the office as my home is a ranch style built in the early 1950s. Unit is quite sturdy and fits well under the wall cabinets. Assembly was straight forward and went together without incident.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for entryway
reviews.reviewText: Sturdy construction, easy to assemble and perfect size for my house entryway, I wish it were made of real wood it does look great though, I am satisfied with the product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for Home Office
reviews.reviewText: I wish all assemblies were this easy, I didn't even need to read the instructions! This is a great shelving unit. Very study, good quality for the price and easy to assemble. Took about 30 minutes. Looks great in the home office, highly recommend!
